726508f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, west side, north from 63rd Avenue. The first house was owned by Campioni (Campone) from 1873 to 1909. The second
house is the F. Miller house of 1873.
View 2 shows the Campioni house, at a later date.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1923
View 2: P. L. Sperr  July 2, 1935
